WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:03.070
In a society facing
overwhelming challenges,

00:00:03.070 --> 00:00:06.420
why do we keep making the same
irrational decisions?

00:00:06.420 --> 00:00:09.120
Why to we repeat destructive behaviors?

00:00:09.120 --> 00:00:13.560
At Carnegie Mellon University,
as pioneers of behavioral economics,

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:16.260
we are advancing decision-making science.

00:00:16.260 --> 00:00:21.250
Our distinct fusion of economics and
psychology is reducing teen pregnancy.

00:00:21.250 --> 00:00:25.360
Simplifying health care and
battling economic injustices.

00:00:25.360 --> 00:00:27.830
We don't just study behavior,
we change it.

00:00:27.830 --> 00:00:29.710
We do the work that matters.

